h
</figureCitation>
). Medial margin of Cx-I with distinct projections associated with setal bases (
<figureCitation id="D7E31DF4FFD3CF10FB64F8D38CEBF895" box="[1164,1270,1870,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,180,1586]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,174,1595]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–c. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 097); a. integument papillae; b. palp; c. coxal and genital field; d.–g. H. poseidon female (MNHN B 16 C); d. integument papillae; e. Cx-I+II; f. III-L-4–6 (detail. trident setae at higher magnification); g. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613330/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Figs 14 e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D7E31DF4FFD3CF10FAEBF8D08D28F895" box="[1283,1333,1869,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1596,1621]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 15. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 151); a. Cx-I+II; b.–d. integument papillae in various views. e.–h. H. poseidon; e. Cx-I+II; f.–h. integument papillae in various views. i.–m. H. sp. inc. nr. lasioderma (MD 061); i. Cx-I+II; k.–m. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613332/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">15 e</figureCitation>
). Genital field with very numerous Ac (100 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FDF1F8EF8A3AF870" bold="true" box="[537,551,1906,1932]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
180 pairs, maximum n per transect, 7 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FC38F8EF8BC3F870" bold="true" box="[976,990,1906,1932]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
12); sexual dimorphism in genital plate setae number and density: 
<specimenCount id="59DECAF8FFD3CF10FE55F80A89FAF84D" box="[445,487,1943,1969]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
50 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FDE0F80B8A0BF84C" bold="true" box="[520,534,1942,1968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
70 (ratio n/plate L 0.20 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FCFBF80B8B3CF84C" bold="true" box="[787,801,1942,1968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
0.28), 
<specimenCount id="59DECAF8FFD3CF10FC80F80A8B8FF84D" box="[872,914,1943,1969]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
35 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FC5CF80B8BDFF84C" bold="true" box="[948,962,1942,1968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
50 (ratio 0.14 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FBBFF80B8C78F84C" bold="true" box="[1111,1125,1942,1968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
0.16). Leg segments slender (e.g., L/H ratio I-L-5, 4.5 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FE5EF82789D9F828" bold="true" box="[438,452,1978,2004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
6.1; II-L-5, 5.9 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FD86F8278A61F828" bold="true" box="[622,636,1978,2004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
7.3; III-L-5, 5.0 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FCC7F8278B20F828" bold="true" box="[815,829,1978,2004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
7.0; IV-L-5, 6.5 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD3CF10FC07F8278BE0F828" bold="true" box="[1007,1021,1978,2004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
8.4). Distal edges of I-IV-L-4-5 with thickened, bi- or trifurcated setae, particularly strongly developed and trident-shaped at III-L-5 (
<figureCitation id="D7E31DF4FFD3CF10FB3CF8438D24F805" box="[1236,1337,2014,2041]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,180,1586]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,174,1595]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–c. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 097); a. integument papillae; b. palp; c. coxal and genital field; d.–g. H. poseidon female (MNHN B 16 C); d. integument papillae; e. Cx-I+II; f. III-L-4–6 (detail. trident setae at higher magnification); g. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613330/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 14 f</figureCitation>
); ventral setae of IV-L-4-5 elongated; swimming setae (anterior/posterior) II-L-5, 0/1; III-L-4, 0/9-13; III-L-5, 0/6-9; IV-L- 4, 6-12/6-11; IV-L-5, 0[-1]/5-8; claw length (all legs) 23-30; L ratio claw/ I-IV-L-5, 6-13 [mean: 8] % (see 
<figureCitation id="D7E31DF4FFD4CF17FAA4FF208D81FF2B" box="[1356,1436,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,180,1586]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,174,1595]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–c. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 097); a. integument papillae; b. palp; c. coxal and genital field; d.–g. H. poseidon female (MNHN B 16 C); d. integument papillae; e. Cx-I+II; f. III-L-4–6 (detail. trident setae at higher magnification); g. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613330/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
f-g).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07C252FAFFD4CF17FF2FFE998B27F81D" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD4CF17FF2FFE998CBAFE77" blockId="28.[151,1437,152,648]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD4CF17FF2FFE998946FEE3" bold="true" box="[199,347,260,287]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Description:</emphasis>
Colour unknown. Lateral eyes lens diameter anterior 35-50, posterior 30-45, separation 70-200. Tips of Cx-I with 4-5 strong setae. Groups of similar setae at anterior (about 5) and posterior edge of Cx-II (about 8) and Cx-III (6, resp. 2, slightly finer and shorter). Posterior margin of Cx-IV with 15-20 setae in a single, locally double row, posterolateral apodeme very long, subparallel to median axis or slightly oblique.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD4CF17FF2FFE088D64FD7B" blockId="28.[151,1437,152,648]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Measurements: Male: Idiosoma L/W 1125/1000; Cx-I+II, 270-290/170-180; Cx-III+IV, 280-310/300-310; genital plate 245-250/110-120, genital field with 120-140 pairs of acetabula (8-9 per transect) and 50-70 pairs of medial setae. Distal leg segments, given as L/H (ratio): I-L-4, 155-165/50-55 (3.0-3.1); I-L-5, 210-225/43-45 (4.9-5.2); II- L-4, 230-265/53-55 (4;3-4.8); II-L-5, 285-315/45-50 (6.3-6.6); III-L-4, 225-235/55 (4.1-4.3); III-L-5, 274-350/48- 50 (5.8-7.0); IV-L-4, 293-315/53-55 (5.3-6.0); IV-L-5, 315-350/45-48 (7.0-7.4). Mouthparts: Gnathosoma L 190- 200; chelicera no data; palp total L 433-438; L/H (ratio) P-1, 48-53/55-63 (0.8-0.9); P-2, 73-75/55-58 (1.3-1.4); P-3, 44-48/50 (0.9-1.0); P-4, 180-185/38-40 (4.6-4.9); P-5, 80-83/18 (2.2-2.3); L ratio P-2/P-4, 0.4, P-4/P-5, 2.2-2.3.</paragraph>
<caption id="1BA751F9FFD4CF17FF7FF9A18BB3F961" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613332" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3613332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613332/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" startId="28.[151,250,1596,1621]" targetBox="[151,1436,661,1576]" targetPageId="28">
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD4CF17FF7FF9A18BB3F961" blockId="28.[151,1437,1596,1693]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD4CF17FF7FF9A1893DF9A9" bold="true" box="[151,288,1596,1621]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">FIGURE 15.</emphasis>
Family 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD4CF17FE9DF9A18A05F9A9" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1936" box="[373,536,1596,1621]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hydrodromidae</taxonomicName>
, genus 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD4CF17FD8CF9A18AF8F9A8" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1837" box="[612,741,1596,1620]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD4CF17FD8CF9A18AF8F9A8" box="[612,741,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Hydrodroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. a.–d. 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD4CF17FCC2F9A08BC6F9A8" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[810,987,1596,1620]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenoderma">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD4CF17FCC2F9A08BC6F9A8" box="[810,987,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. amoenoderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, female (MD 151); a. Cx-I+II; b.–d. integument papillae in various views. e.–h. 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD4CF17FDF0F9FC8A8EF984" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[536,659,1632,1656]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poseidon">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD4CF17FDF0F9FC8A8EF984" box="[536,659,1632,1656]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. poseidon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; e. Cx-I+II; f.–h. integument papillae in various views. i.–m. 
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD4CF17FAF9F9FC8D66F984" box="[1297,1403,1633,1656]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. sp. inc.</emphasis>
nr. 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD4CF17FF7FF9198914F960" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,265,1668,1692]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lasioderma">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD4CF17FF7FF9198914F960" box="[151,265,1668,1692]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">lasioderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MD 061); i. Cx-I+II; k.–m. integument papillae in various views.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD4CF17FF2FF9568B27F81D" blockId="28.[151,1437,1738,2017]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Female: Idiosoma L/W 1200-1500/ 
<date id="3B6627B1FFD4CF17FDBFF9578ACDF919" box="[599,720,1738,1765]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1000" valueMax="1375">1000-1375</date>
; Cx-I+II, 280-365/180-210; Cx-III+IV, 280-380/300-370; genital plate 230-330/110-160, genital field with 100-175 pairs of acetabula (7-12 per transect) and 35-50 pairs of medial setae. Distal leg segments, given as L/H (ratio): I-L-4, 170-213/55-65 (3.1-3.3); I-L-5, 225-320/48-53 (4.5-6.1); II-L-4, 255-320/58-73 (4.1-4.8); II-L-5, 295-375/48-55 (5.8-7.3); III-L-4, 245-295/63-70 (3.9-4.6); III-L-5, 250- 370/50-60 (5.0-6.8); IV-L-4, 295-405/55-70 (5.4-6.4); IV-L-5, 325-430/50-55 (6.5-8.4). Mouthparts: Gnathosoma L 210-260; chelicera L 298-368, L/H 4.6-4.9, basal segment/claw L ratio 3.6-4.3; palp total L 500-530; L/H (ratio) P-1, 53-65/65-70 (0.8-1.0); P-2, 83-93/60-65 (1.4); P-3, 53-55/55-60 (0.9-1.0); P-4, 210-223/43-45 (4.8-5.1); P-5, 90-95/19-20 (4.4-4.9); L ratio P-2/P-4, 0.4, P-4/P-5, 2.3-2.4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07C252FAFFD5CF16FF2FFF0589A7FF2B" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD5CF16FF2FFF0589A7FF2B" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FF2FFF0589BBFF4F" bold="true" box="[199,422,152,179]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Derivatio nominis:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FE44FF048A09FF4F" box="[428,532,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Poseidon</emphasis>
(Greek: Ποσειδῶν), Greek god of the sea with a trident-shaped spear, like the leg setae of this 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FECCFF2089AEFF2B" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1837" box="[292,435,189,215]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FECCFF2089AEFF2B" box="[292,435,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Hydrodroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07C252FAFFD5CF16FF2FFF7C89F2FBEF" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD5CF16FF2FFF7C8977FE53" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FF2FFF7C8920FF07" bold="true" box="[199,317,225,251]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks:</emphasis>
In integument structure, shape and setation of coxae, leg proportions (rather slender segments and relatively short claws) and swimming setation (numerous, but only one posterior on II-L-5 and absent from anterior surface of IV-L-5), 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FE9EFEB789E2FEBF" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[374,511,297,323]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poseidon">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FE9EFEB789E2FEBF" box="[374,511,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. poseidon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FD3AFEB78B76FEBF" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2004" box="[722,875,297,323]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FD3AFEB78B76FEBF" box="[722,875,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the northern hemisphere. The latter species differs in: (1) lower numbers of Ac (at maximum 70 pairs, 4-7 per transect); (2) absence of a sexual dimorphism in genital setation; (3) a stouter P-4 (L/H ratio &lt;4.5) and (4) distal setae on leg segments more moderately developed, not trident-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD5CF16FF2FFE248C13FDC3" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Another three Madagascan 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FE14FE248A96FE2F" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1837" box="[508,651,441,467]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FE14FE248A96FE2F" box="[508,651,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Hydrodroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are characterized by higher numbers of swimming setae (total n&gt; 35). Among these, 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FE48FE438A50FE0B" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[416,589,477,503]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesembrina">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FE48FE438A50FE0B" box="[416,589,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. mesembrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differs in a smooth medial margin of Cx-I, 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FBA4FE438CC9FE0B" authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2014" box="[1100,1236,477,503]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhokhovi">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FBA4FE438CC9FE0B" box="[1100,1236,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. zhokhovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in an integument with simple papillae and the presence of 2 swimming setae on posterior surface of II-L-5; 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FB93FD9F8D21FDE7" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[1147,1340,513,539]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenoderma">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FB93FD9F8D21FDE7" box="[1147,1340,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. amoenoderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished by the presence of numerous anterior swimming setae on IV-L-5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD5CF16FF2FFDD48A51FC7F" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Both 
<bibRefCitation id="2B497C80FFD5CF16FEEEFDD489D9FD98" author="Lundblad, O." box="[262,452,585,612]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref72161" refString="Lundblad, O. (1946) Madagassische Susswassermilben. Arkiv for Zoologi, 38, A (14), 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1946">Lundblad (1946)</bibRefCitation>
and K.O. 
<bibRefCitation id="2B497C80FFD5CF16FDD3FDD48AD5FD98" author="Viets, K. O." box="[571,712,585,612]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="89 - 120" refId="ref73790" refString="Viets, K. O. (1964) Neue und seltene Wassermilben aus Madagaskar. Le Naturaliste Malgache, 13 (1962), 89 - 120." type="journal article" year="1964">Viets (1964)</bibRefCitation>
reported the presence of 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FC02FDD78C70FD9F" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1946" box="[1002,1133,586,611]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FC02FDD78C70FD9F" box="[1002,1133,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="37CF41E1FFD5CF16FB5CFDD48D20FD9F" box="[1204,1341,585,611]" name="Madagascar" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, considering quadrangular posteromedial apodemes of Cx-I+II as a diagnostic feature of that species (
<bibRefCitation id="2B497C80FFD5CF16FB0DFDF08D85FD7B" author="Lundblad, O." box="[1253,1432,621,647]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref72161" refString="Lundblad, O. (1946) Madagassische Susswassermilben. Arkiv for Zoologi, 38, A (14), 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1946">Lundblad 1946</bibRefCitation>
: absence of such apodemes “as generally known the case also in our common 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FBE9FD0F8C84FD57" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2004" box="[1025,1177,657,683]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FBE9FD0F8C84FD57" box="[1025,1177,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”). As demonstrated by Gerecke (2017), both authors tended to confuse 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FD58FD2B8B5AFD33" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2004" box="[688,839,693,719]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FD58FD2B8B5AFD33" box="[688,839,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FC6EFD2B8CB5FD33" authority="Besseling, 1940" authorityName="Besseling" authorityYear="1940" box="[902,1192,693,719]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FC6EFD2B8BF1FD33" box="[902,1004,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. pilosa</emphasis>
Besseling, 1940
</taxonomicName>
, a species in fact having Cx-I+II with very simple or absent posteromedial apodemes. Instead, such apodemes are well developed in 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FA69FD478911FCEB" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2004" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FA69FD478911FCEB" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Gerecke 2017, 
<figureCitation id="D7E31DF4FFD5CF16FE07FD608A57FCEB" box="[495,586,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1320,1345]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,272,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,265,1301]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Family Eylaidae, genus Eylais (e.–f. from Koenike 1898, without sex and magnification information, modified). a.–b. E. degenerata male (MD 239); a. eye plate; b. palp, P-3–5; c.–d. E. voeltzkowi male (MD 235); c. frontal plate and integument with acetabula on the right side; d. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera; e. E. crenocula, eye plate; f. E. megalostoma, eye plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613306" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613306/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 2 C</figureCitation>
) and not suitable for separating 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FC59FD638C2FFCEB" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1946" box="[945,1074,766,791]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FC59FD638C2FFCEB" box="[945,1074,766,791]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Revision of slide material from SMNH and SMF show that populations recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="37CF41E1FFD5CF16FCEBFCBC8B97FCC7" box="[771,906,801,827]" name="Madagascar" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
under the name of 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FB8DFCBF8CF5FCC7" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1946" box="[1125,1256,802,827]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FB8DFCBF8CF5FCC7" box="[1125,1256,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not have the doubled II-L-5 swimming seta characteristic of the latter. In view of high numbers of acetabula on the genital plates they are here attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FE56FCF78A58FC7F" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[446,581,873,899]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poseidon">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FE56FCF78A58FC7F" box="[446,581,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. poseidon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD5CF16FF2FFC108D22FC13" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
A previously unpublished specimen from Manjakatompo (
<accessionNumber id="508B9C92FFD5CF16FC82FC108BEAFC5B" box="[874,1015,908,935]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/SMF51146" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">SMF 51146</accessionNumber>
), identified by K.O. 
<bibRefCitation id="2B497C80FFD5CF16FB04FC108D67FC54" author="Viets, K. O." box="[1260,1402,909,936]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="89 - 120" refId="ref73790" refString="Viets, K. O. (1964) Neue und seltene Wassermilben aus Madagaskar. Le Naturaliste Malgache, 13 (1962), 89 - 120." type="journal article" year="1964">Viets (1964)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FF7FFC2C89BEFC37" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2004" box="[151,419,945,971]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FF7FFC2C89BEFC37" box="[151,419,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Hydrodroma despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is also a representative of 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FD30FC2F8B7DFC37" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[728,864,945,971]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poseidon">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FD30FC2F8B7DFC37" box="[728,864,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. poseidon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From our present knowledge, 
<taxonomicName id="88D87AF2FFD5CF16FB2BFC2F8D46FC37" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2004" box="[1219,1371,945,971]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FB2BFC2F8D46FC37" box="[1219,1371,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the W Palaearctic, all African records under this name refer to different species (Gerecke 2017).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F670171FFD5CF16FF2FFC6589F2FBEF" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1115]" box="[199,495,1016,1043]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="7DACDD63FFD5CF16FF2FFC658931FBEF" bold="true" box="[199,300,1016,1043]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Habitat:</emphasis>
Standing waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
